Take care of yourself Jim. You're getting a bit looney.  Also what culture will you appropriate and monetize off next? Asian food?

They serve large dishes and for reasonable rates. helpful staff. 5 stars from me.
This team is smashing the game. Drinks are super on point, food is great. Perfect for a tapas and cocktails kinda night.
Amazing service, food, and ambiance! Highly recommend this place!

Went on a Thursday night early in March. Party of 2. We had the shrimp enchiladas and the beef-cheese-mix empanadas, followed by the churros to share. Food was great! Only reason I docked a star is because the waitress seemed a bit pushy, as to moving quickly, even when there was no shortage of open tables around. Otherwise all good. Came to 50$ with tip and taxes, and that's pretty cheap for NYC.
Love-hate relationship with this place; the food is fantastic, but they close way too early.  The jalapeño margaritas are the best I’ve ever had, but they close way too early.
Great food and atmosphere. We were looking forward to seeing Cramer, but such was not the case...Looking forward to our next visit..
Great spot and great team. Food is surprisingly good, so don't underestimate or overlook it. Well worth checking it out.
Amazing drinks highly recommend Cute atmosphere Tacos was good But stake was  nahhhh
Very nice place, small, well designed and clean, with an excellent cocktail menu focusing on mezcal and tequila. The Negroni with Mezcal was amazing.
Meh.

We visited during our recent trip to NYC to celebrate our twin boys 16th bday. My husband is a big Kramer fan and this was a must stop for him.  Keely, our waitress/bartender was amazing and very welcoming and the food delicious. Definitely recommend this place! Scott from Florida!
Very chill, comfortable, with great tequila and mezcal.  Excellent downtempo neighborhood spot.
Food (empanadas, enchiladas, vegi. Tostadas) was great, churros were good too.

Local fav. Comfort Mexican fare. I recommend the beef empanadas and the pork quesadilla. The house margarita is deliciously tart. The Mezcal options are splendid. You will leave happier than how you arrived.

Sorry we missed you Jim when we were there with Bob Lang and the Explosive Options Team!  Your staff is always amazing, Nicole, Jake and the rest of your team was amazing and the food and margaritas were spectacular!  Great-Great time!  Thanks!
The food was amazing and the service was spectacular. Great place, I recommend you go!
Great customer service and fabulous margaritas
Friendly attentive service.
Good place. Good food.
Sui generous Mexican tapas.  The Goldman of fast serve Mexican bar food and craft tequila bebidas!
Relaxed, cosy atmosphere. Good food, not enormous portions. Great staff.
Good place

The atmosphere is fine. I ordered tacos and a beer. Very excited to eat and then I got 2 tiny tacos and a little salad for $11... this place doesn’t classify as a taperia or small plates so I was disappointed. The taste of the food was fine. Service was great. Bathroom is clean.
Really great staff, great drinks and overall a good time.

Tacos were overpriced. Ordered to-go for myself and my co-worker and one order only had one taco in it (two tortillas but one was missing the filling). Great bar atmosphere though and amazing tequila selection.
Overpriced, portions  of  food very small.

Excellent spot. Cozy without being crowded. Bartender Jake is really nice. Awesome drinks and food.
Cozy bar with friendly barstaff and an awesome mezcal selection.
Food and drink were exceptional. Enjoyed the experience.

For our first time being there it was worth what was spent. The food portion was quite small and its was overpriced for what we ordered. Sadly we heard this was a good place for food and drinks. Don't think so.

We had an UNBELIEVABLE experience. Oscar absolutely hooked us up, and after finding out that my husband was an enormously huge Cramer fan, went even further above and beyond to give us an incredible evening. Food was fantastic (pork quesidillas changed my life and the margaritas were awesome!!!)
Amazing food. Staff create the best atmosphere. Did I mention the amazing food?
Great Tequila Bar with even better cocktails
Great atmosphere and very tasty Mexican food and drinks

Nothing special. The decor is a facade to mask food that's not much better than something microwaved from the frozen food aisle at the grocery store. In fact, I'm pretty sure they microwave a lot of the food they serve. The drinks are bad, and the food is not spicy. Is this Mexican?
Love this place!! Great tequila selection, great food!!! Can’t wait to go back!!!

We got 2 pitchers of margs and a bunch of tacos to try! I ate the fried chicken taco and a pork taco (I believe). They were aiiiiiiight! The atmosphere and vibes were better than the tacos.The marg wasn't that strong, but hey, we still had a good time!
Great hidden gem. Jake and his staff were awesome. The food was delicious, I had the short ribs, very tasty. The Tequila drinks were great too.  Definitely worth a try.
Wonderful
Dope bartender good snacks. All over it
Great crowd, yummy food and great bartender!
Great quesadilla and home made chips. Also the patio felt really nice in the scorching summer heat, and they had authentic Fanta Naranja, yum!
Amazing service. Jake was so nice!!! Definitely come by for some delicious margaritas on the back patio!
Awesome tacos.  Nice little relaxing bar.  Wish they included a 3rd taco.   Missed Cramer.   Booooyyyyyyeeerrr!!!!!!!!
Excellent margarita, rice and beans, and empanadas. Service was very friendly and competent.
It doesn't get better than fresh food with simple and delicious ingredients. Whether you are looking for a high-end tequila cocktail or a bite to eat, you cannot go wrong with Bar San Miguel.

Fantastic service, our server was really patient with our group (which was great as we arrived after having a few fishbowls) and she recommended some great snacks.  We also had a situation with a ring getting lost in the sink and another server jumped in to save the night. He got it out from the sink trap and I couldn't be more thankful for him going above and beyond for us!
Tony the bartender was very nice and kind And very professional

After hearing about Bar San Miguel for some time, I knew i had to try it.  On my trip to New York this week I finally had an opportunity to stop by.  I was not disappointed.  The food was excellent as were the drinks.  The atmosphere was warm and inviting.  Great Staff!  Keep up the good work.

Great food, great drinks, excellent service! It's a nice setting with seating inside and outside. Cozy place and very comfortable. I got the enchiladas and they were great, just thought they were a little small. Otherwise excellent place!

Fan of Cramerica so our family of 4 decided to visit while in the area.  Food was tasty, especially the Puerco, but way overpriced for the portion size.  I ordered  Rose wine while awaiting my order and was very disappointed to see 1 1/2" of wine in a small wineglass that cost $9, totally ridiculous.  The waiter was friendly and attentive and the place was busy but nice and quiet.
Food portion was too small. Overpriced & none of the salsas were spicy at all. Ordered the Carne De Reyes & literally only had 3 pieces of "mashed" potatoes. Not worth your money guys 👎

Incredibly poorly managed for a restaurant owned by a guy who pontificates as if he is a management guru. Cramer apparently can't even manage a taco stand well enough to produce consistently decent food.  Hey Cramer - did you know Mexican food is supposed to be a bit spicier than cardboard that has been sitting in a warehouse since the Great Depression?  A taste test between Bar San Miguel and my daughter's school lunch would probably result in most people thinking Bar San Miguel's food is made with leftovers - from last year.  The food I ordered was flavorless - as was that ordered by others I was with. I ordered something that had potatoes. I found the variance in the temperature of those potatoes to indicate they were microwaved - some were hot, some were cold. What garbage!  Like many places in Brooklyn, this place is not a bargain. But what sets this place apart, it seems, is that it is owned by a blow-hard hypocrite who cannot even manage a tiny business while he's blabbering on TV as if he's the world's greatest investment mind.  Next time you want Mexican food, skip this over-priced dump and get some street food that will likely taste better and cost 1/3 the price.  If you don't believe this review, check out Yelp. There are many horrible reviews. And many of the reviews that are hidden as "not currently recommended" are very interesting - and negative.

If Jim Cramer's pet project were a publicly traded company, he'd lambaste it as a fraud. If only the food were half as good as the pictures the restaurants posts on Yelp - but it's not.  The food didn't make me sick, but next time I hear Cramer promote his restaurant on Mad Money, I might throw up.  The quality control is garbage at Jim Cramer's Bar San Miguel, and there are obviously insufficient systems in place to monitor the quality.  I ordered the short rib tacos. 1) They were appetizer-size. 2) They had almost no meat. 3) They were virtually flavorless.  My friend ordered a chicken dish with mole sauce. What was that like? 1) The chicken was barely warm, 2) The mole sauce was flavorless, and cold, 3) The potatoes it came with ranged in temperature from hot to cold (gee, did they nuke it?).  Cramer - you need to stick to what you do best. This restaurant is an embarrassment.  If you want better food, go to a street vendor. At least there the owner actually knows what's going on, and cares.
Great cocktails! Jake & Zac are master oncologists. Tequila tequila tequila
Good food!
Great food, cocktails and friendly staff!
Limited menu selection, Food is ok. Cool ambiance!
Cute, quaint spot. There's a backyard available for seating. Empanadas were pretty good and filling.
Amy rocks best Margarita ever from scratch
Great drinks and good food from what I tried. The bartender was super friendly and the playlist he had going was awesome
Very nice bar with a backyard patio. Relaxed atmosphere and friendly staff.
Boo yaaah Mr Cramer. Great food, good service, great atmosphere. We will definitely be coming back soon. I will have to admit, we enjoyed watching you play waiter; you may have missed your calling.
Really tasty food, great inventive drink menu, and a wonderful atmosphere, especially at Halloween. And every now and then, you might run into Jim Cramer, one of the investors in the restaurant.

I recently had my Day of the Dead themed bridal shower at Bar San Miguel and it was everything I had wanted and more! My guests and I felt so welcome and taken care of.  I have been hearing rave reviews from my friends since my shower regarding the food, drinks, warm service, and fabulous personality of Bar San Miguel.  Jeremy, Regina, Lin, and the kitchen staff turned out delicious drinks and food flawlessly and kept the energy warm and exciting.
Hey skeeeedaddy the establishment owned by CNBCs Jim Cramer is not just a novelty spot but is a super hip spot with a great hip vibe and tasty finger foods and beer /tequila.
Nice little bar, the drinks and dessert are good.

Go for the drinks especially the happy hour. The staff is very congenial. The bartender is very entertaining.  The food was very mediocre. Guacamole had a weird taste like there may have been mayonnaise in it. I tried adding lime juice, hot sauce and salt and couldn't fix it.  The shrimp in the Camarones Diablo was tasteless, as in the shrimp had no flavor at all. The Diablo sauce had one note, dry crushed chillies. The skirt steak was small for the price with weird mix of green beans and raw baby spinach on the side. But the potatoes were very well done. They should serve a bowl of the taters, sprinkled with Tajin and some chipolte mayo.  The longanisa tacos were the best dish even though they used pre-formed taco shells and there was a lot of the aforementioned guacamole on the dish.  Rice and beans were inoffensive.
Best Mexican food great atmosphere amazing mezcal and my most favorite glass of red wine - that Nebbiolo...

I love this place. Happy hour is the bomb. The guy that owns the bar, Patrick, is very friendly and he kills it with his sangria. It's not overly sugary, which i think ends up tasting cheap. It's a dark red, and very strong sangria,  that they give to you in a goblet. Do reccomend.
Mexican done right! Great food, great drinks, great service.
I love this place. It's currently my favorite Mexican food in Brooklyn. The empanadas are my favorite thing on the menu.

My dad is a huge Jim Cramer fan.  Because my dad watches Cramer religiously, he knew that Cramer had become an investor/owner in Bar San Miguel.  When my dad came to visit, my wife and I made sure we took him here with the hope that we would meet Cramer.  Unfortunately, Cramer was not "working" that night.  Even though Cramer wasn't there, we were very impressed with BSM.  Our server was very nice; he even gave us a couple free drinks because of a mistaken order at another table.  The Manhattan was amazing.  It is probably the best drink I've had in NYC.  The noise level was better than most places as it seems to be geared to a more sophisticated crowd.  BSM consists of a bar with stools and then tables.  This isn't a bar where you'll have a hundred people standing in a tight space.  I am excited to go back to BSM in the future.  Maybe Cramer will be there next time.  We can only hope.
